16
00:00:32.885 --> 00:00:34.805
I don't expect you know
anything about computers.

17
00:00:34.805 --> 00:00:36.830
I think no matter
what your background

18
00:00:36.830 --> 00:00:39.065
is, you can program.

19
00:00:39.065 --> 00:00:40.790
That's why it's called
Programming for

20
00:00:40.790 --> 00:00:43.130
Everybody. I have
a couple of goals.

21
00:00:43.130 --> 00:00:45.740
Certainly, I want to
teach you how to program.

22
00:00:45.740 --> 00:00:47.750
But actually what I
really want to do

23
00:00:47.750 --> 00:00:49.625
is teach you how to take
a programming class

24
00:00:49.625 --> 00:00:51.530
because it turns out that most of

25
00:00:51.530 --> 00:00:54.350
the other programming classes
in the world are kind of difficult.

26
00:00:54.350 --> 00:00:56.785
They sort of assume way too
much and the teachers sort of

27
00:00:56.785 --> 00:00:58.330
don't even realize how much

28
00:00:58.330 --> 00:01:00.110
they're expecting from students.

29
00:01:00.110 --> 00:01:02.720
So when you're done
with this class,

30
00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:05.855
you can go and take
another beginning class.

31
00:01:05.855 --> 00:01:07.775
And that way you have this as an

32
00:01:07.775 --> 00:01:10.110
on-ramp to all of your
programming activity.

33
00:01:10.110 --> 00:01:12.340
And so I'm really excited
that you're here.

34
00:01:12.340 --> 00:01:14.390
Another thing that I
want to do is I want

35
00:01:14.390 --> 00:01:15.965
