36
00:01:15.965 --> 00:01:18.800
I want to teach you how to
be a teacher of programming.

37
00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:21.140
So I want you to
take all my ideas,

38
00:01:21.140 --> 00:01:23.195
and I want to you to
help the next person.

39
00:01:23.195 --> 00:01:25.865
And the reason is that
learning how to program

40
00:01:25.865 --> 00:01:30.930
is a little sort of foggy,

41
00:01:30.930 --> 00:01:34.230
uncomfortable, you
get stuck on things,

42
00:01:34.230 --> 00:01:37.020
and those things aren't
hard, I assure you.

43
00:01:37.020 --> 00:01:38.340
But when you're stuck on them,

44
00:01:38.340 --> 00:01:39.750
they feel really hard.

45
00:01:39.750 --> 00:01:41.270
And the best way to get unstuck

46
00:01:41.270 --> 00:01:42.815
